<h4>
    Thermal Expansion of Liquids
</h4>

<p class="definition">
    <strong>Mercury</strong>
    <br><br>
    A silver, toxic metal.
    The only metal that is liquid at room temperature.
    Experiences very significant thermal expansion and contraction.
</p>
<p class="definition">
    <strong>Thermometer</strong>
    <br><br>
    Originally, a thermometer consisted of mercy in a vial.
    (It is now mostly digital or something less toxic)
    <br><br>
    Due to thermal expansion and contraction of a liquid,
    the mercury would get larger and smaller when the room was warmer and cooler.
</p>
